referenced                     in the FEMA guidelines for flood hazard mapping, appendix A.                     The Institute of Applied Geospatial Technology performed a                     ground control analysis of the Tompkins County LiDAR data                     using ground control checkpoints in several land cover                     classes and found the resultant RMSE in the exposed ground                     class to be within the contract specifications of 0.185                     meters.</vertaccr>                 <qvertpa>                     <vertaccv>0.185 m RMSE</vertaccv>                     <vertacce>Vertical error associated with this LiDAR data set                         is a function of several variables including acquisition                         parameters and practices, system calibration, GPS                         reference station coordinates, and GPS/INS post                         processing.</vertacce>                 </qvertpa>             </vertacc>         </posacc>          <lineage>             <procstep>                 <procdesc>Topographic contour lines from county-wide ESRI file                     geodatabase were converted to a shapefile, then simplified                     (generalized) using a tolerance of 0.5 feet, then clipped to                     the Town's 500-foot buffer (also including the City of                     Ithaca).
